Responsibility:

Handle multiple client projects such as video production, influencer activation, social media management, and other digital marketing campaigns;
Provide creative inputs in social media content and campaign planning;
Manage timeline to ensure smooth project execution;
Prepare proposals and support new clients pitching;
Liaise with and provide creative briefings to vendors, designers, internal and external parties;
Monitor project implementation and performance against KPIs;
Compile regular and post-campaign reports for project performance evaluations;
Stay alert to industry happenings and able to share insights; 

Requirement: 

Degree in Media, Marketing, Communications or related discipline;
Minimum 1 year experience on digital/social media management or other relevant work experience;
Demonstrate strong communication and presentation skills;
Familiar with the social media & influencer landscape and practices in Hong Kong; 
Proficiency in written and spoken English and Chinese; 
Proactive, passionate, and a detail-minded team player;
Good multi-tasking skills, willing to work under pressure and tight schedules;
Experience working with social listening and social media management tools is a plus;  
Immediate availability is highly preferred;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Account Executive;

All personal data collected will be kept confidential and used for recruitment purpose only.

Being a crucial member of the team, the successful candidate will be responsible for implementing media placements, liaising with client, creative agency, and media vendor to make campaign GO LIVES. We also aim to provide best services and value to our client.
Training on negotiation process and usage on proprietary tools will be provided. This entry-level opportunity will kick-start your career in media and provide a platform to partner with the world’s leading consumer brands.

Qualifications and Requirements:

Passion for advertising / media
Form 7 / Diploma / University graduated in any discipline;
Fluent in English and Chinese, both written and spoken language skills;   
Detail oriented, organised and sensitive to numbers;
A good team player with good communication skills and self-motivated;

Job Scope:

Liaise with both traditional and digital media vendors on buying cost
Optimisation of media budget and provide the best value / solution for client;
Participate in implementing an integrated traditional and digital advertising campaign from material co-ordination, booking, post campaign reporting / evaluation to monthly billing
Keep monitoring the advertising market change, client’s competitors move and the transformation of media consumption behavior
Initiate “out-of-box” ideas to your client

We offer 5 days’ work week, good salary package with MPF and Medical Plan with Dental Care and staff training for development.  Interested applicants should submit resumes with expected salary and date of availability to our email address (please indicate the relevant job position: Media Executive Buying & Operation Team)

For further information about IPG Mediabrands, please visit: http://www.ipgmediabrands.com/

Planning



Assist the Manager to develop media strategy, channel/ platform recommendations and prepare the detailed media flow-plan;
Leverage available planning tools and liaise with media owners for proposals;
Engage clients on day to day operations, media trend updates and various campaign reports on local/regional/global levels.

Buying



Negotiate with media owners for better rates and value adds;
Book ads - both managed service and self-service across various platforms;
Liaise with media vendors & creative agencies for material submission;
Digital ad ops (campaign set up on self-serve platforms, tagging of ads and client's site, ensure ads are properly served and tags are firing);
Global ops (adhering and following globally set parameters and campaign execution processes while also guiding others);
Oversee all performance across channels (Search, Social, Programmatic etc.);
Monitor and optimize performance during campaign period across platforms such as Google Adwords, Facebook, LinkedIn etc.
Weekly digital reporting, end of campaign reporting and reconciliation of final costs for finance billings.

Qualifications


1 - 3 years' of digital media experience
Meticulous, good with numbers and able to organise and prioritise tasks and work under tight timelines
Resilient to change and willing to keen to learn new skills
Strong communication skills, both written and verbal, with internal and external parties
Ready to take up initiatives and ownership of projects
Play well with others and are a team player
Good command of English and Chinese

Job Description:

Assist manager to prepare and execute digital advertising campaigns;
Work closely with vendors and internal teams to plan, develop and execute digital marketing projects;
Meet and liaise with clients to ensure client satisfaction;
Coordinate with art directors and social media editors to develop social media contents; 
Responsible for committed timelines and deliverable throughout projects;
Prepare advertising plans for search, display, video and social media ads;
Other ad-hoc assignments.


Requirements:

Strong Responsibility in handling projects; 
Have experience in managing one or more of below digital marketing channels is preferred: Facebook, Instagram, KOL, micro influencer, video production, Google Adwords or Forum;
1 - 3 years working experience in an agency or in a marketing position;
Good project management and communication skill;
Attention to details and ability to work under tight timeline and multi-task independently;
Knowledge in video or photo editing is a plus.

Benefits:

Five-day work week
Birthday Leave
Bank holidays
Shuttle Bus to/from work

Location: Kwai Chung

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Job Description


Plan and execute integrated digital marketing strategies for clients on different platforms, including but not limited to Search Engine, Display and Social Media;
Setup and manage Google Ads, Yahoo & Bing campaigns;
Analyze media performances with different tracking tools such as Google Analytics;
Handle reports with insights on an ad-hoc / weekly / monthly basis;
Prepare pitching materials and review with clients on media performance + formulate strategies on optimization;
Prepare presentation deck and materials for client pitching.
The Successful Applicant

Bachelor's degree;
Good command of both spoken and written Chinese and English, native English is an advantage;

Minimum 1 year of experience in digital advertising field or advertising agency;

Experience in Google Ads / Yahoo / Bing advertising campaign management and Google Analytics is an advantage;

Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;
Proficient in Microsoft Excel and PowerPoint;

Immediate availability is preferred.

What's On Offer


Attractive Remuneration Package and Benefits
5-day work
Bank Holidays and other special leave (e.g. Birthday Leave, Family Leave, etc...)
Medical Insurance
Sales and Product Training will be provided
Team Building Activites
Opportunity for Job Promotion
Friendly Work Environment
Interest parties please send your CV with availability, current and expected salary to us. 


