Account Executive

The qualified candidate should have strong interest in digital advertising, high written and verbal communications proficiency in English and Chinese (Mandarin is a plus), as well as being intuitive and creative within the Internet marketing field.  You should be confident with the ability to communicate effectively with clients to meet their needs, and leverage internal resources to achieve the assigned objectives. 



Responsibilities include:


Execute all aspects of digital media campaigns across different channels, such as Facebook, Google, YouTube, etc.;
Prepare text ad copies for search engine marketing, social media and others web content writing;
Provide in-depth analysis to get insights using all obtainable analytics tools;
Assist Account Manager to achieve campaign objectives through close monitoring and frequent optimizations;
Deep dive into campaign analysis to proactively troubleshoot, identify problems, and present solutions to clients;
Leverage internal resources to deliver integrated advertising services to clients;

 
Requirements:       


University Degree in Communication, Marketing or other relevant fields is preferred;
Experience in Advertising & Marketing industry is a plus;
Passionate about digital marketing;
Proficient in Chinese language (Traditional & Simplified) and English is a must (Mandarin is a plus);
Proven skills in analyzing large quantities of data, making recommendations, and offering strategic consultation;
Excellent communication, problem solving, organizational, and time management skills;
Passionate about Internet and latest online advertising technologies;
Ability to work under pressure by handling multiple assignments and meeting tight deadlines;
Self-motivated and problem solver, with strong CAN DO spirit;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Senior Account Executive;



All personal data collected will be kept confidential and used for recruitment purpose only.

Our client is one of the biggest local insurance company and they are expanding their Digital team across web marketing, performance marketing and content marketing. They are now looking for a high caliber to join their digital acquisition team to drive innovation in ecommerce and performance marketing.

Responsibilities:

To plan and implement digital marketing campaign strategy for business development and set clear measurable KPIs;
To keep up with digital trends, competitive activities, and best practices to drive innovation in performance marketing;
To leverage CRM platforms to deliver personalised and relevant content to audience;
To set up measurements and drive performance of all digital marketing campaigns and our e-commerce site to achieve traffic and digital lead KPIs;
To expand new customers and retain existing customers through driving digital marketing campaigns and the integration of social and mobile channels;
To liaise with various levels of management and be responsible for implementing strategic change aligned with the firm wise digital strategic goals;
To track and monitor the effectiveness of all digital marketing efforts against business goals;
To present category/campaign business results and insights to senior leaders and executives on a regular basis including scorecards, testing results, new initiatives, business reviews, etc.

Requirements:

Bachelor's degree in Marketing, ecommerce or Business management;
At least 7 years of experience of E-commerce and Performance Marketing, within financial services is a plus;
Core business strategy skills for strategy definition, roadmap development, budget planning, success measurement, etc.
Strong analytical and quantitative skills; ability to use customer and acquisition data and business metrics to support business decisions, optimization and generate insights;
Successful track record of helping develop, present and execute strategic digital campaigns, deep understanding of the E-Commerce sales & digital marketing channels;
Familiar with media agency performance checking for digital marketing campaign activities;
Digital savvy and with an analytical mindset;
Structured thinker with strong problem-solving skills;
Excellent presentation and communication skills;

Interested individuals can click apply now or send through updated resume in WORD format to Jason.tsui@connectedgroup.com. For a more comprehensive list of current opportunities, please visit www.connectedgroup.com

Responsibilities:

Develop creative ideas and contents for brand promotions on social media platforms;
Plan and execute creative digital marketing campaigns and effective content distribution strategy;
Plan and implement outbound and inbound digital marketing activities by demonstrating expertise

Requirements:

Diploma or above in any disciplines;
Relevant experience / knowledge in marketing and social media is an advantage;
Familiar with China social media (Wechat / Weibo / Douyin / Xiaohongshu / Dianping) is compulsory;
Good communication skills, presentable, result-oriented and able to work under pressure;
Welcome Fresh graduate & Mainland China graduates (IANG);
More experience will be considered as Marketing Executive

We offer attractive remuneration package to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your full resume with present and expected salary by clicking 'Apply Now'

Personal information collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Responsibilities:

Manage the performance of a portfolio of programmatic and ad network partners for global new user acquisition campaigns;
Monitor budget distribution and performance of paid-ad campaigns;
Recommend app install and in-app engagement campaigns optimizations and run A/B tests accordingly;
Maintain relationship with existing advertising agency / partners and leverage their performance by providing insight from internal reports;
Expand paid channels, able to acquire new paid media sources;
Able to pull and analyze the data and gain insights from the data;
Identify market opportunities for acquisition growth;
Assist in performing day-to-day optimization efforts to meet campaign objectives;
Experiment and identify channels to test, running tests, performing customer / audience segmentation analysis, developing social media presence, and finding ways to optimize paid channels.
Requirements:

Degree in marketing, mass communications or related discipline;
2+ years' paid media advertising in overseas markets, mobile-app preferred but not a must;
Strong analytical skills, with a data-driven and strategic mindset particularly for consumer insights and business growth;
User-focused and product-driven: strong understanding of product, technology, platform and audience;
Independent, attentive to details and self-motivated;
Energetic with can-do attitude and team spirit;
Strong communication skills in English and Mandarin;
Candidates from marketing agencies are welcome.
We offer:

5 days work
13-21 days annual leave
Discretionary bonus
Festival cash incentives
Full-paid sick leave
Marriage leave
Compassionate leave
Medical insurance
Dental scheme
WFH policy
